This is such a perfect soundboard! What a wonderful MN show! Incredible sound, thanks for uploading, though I must say nothing annoys me more than having an incredible file like this and then to have it lazily labeled and presented, I realize it was probably forgotten and unnoticed, accidents happen. But still, UNNACCEPTABLE!!!!!!!!!!! Jk I’m not that weird, but really this is a great show and I am loving that beautiful ‘82 energy. I’ve been going through every MN show because for some reason they often have some really incredible moments that often go under the radars of most Live-Dead-listening Deadheads, so with that in mind, it’s always worth checking out Minnesota shows. In fact, MN is home to a lot of uncommon knowledge historical-Grateful-Dead significances, Bobby met his future wife at one (some say this one, “I met her accidentally in St Paul, MN”, and on 10/19/71 they debuted Keith Godchaux for his first ever live show with the band at Northrop Auditorium, and that one is a brilliant ‘71 show when you get the chance, because not only did it debut Keith, it debut six (6!) NEW original Grateful Dead songs, those six songs are: Tennesee Jed, Jack Straw, Mexicali Blues, Comes a Time, One More Saturday Night, AND Ramble On Rose, those all made their live debut performances that night. I think that is among the top two or three shows with the most original debut performances, the other being 2/9/73 - with: Row Jimmy, Loose Lucy, Here Comes Sunshine, TLEO, Eyes of the World, China Doll, and Wave That Flag. Not sure if that’s the most and 10/19/71 is the second most or what but my data is telling me so. 

Anyway, back to ‘82, keep them jams coming! That year is a surprisingly hot one. 

Also if OP can fix the song titles at the end of Set 2, that’d be grrrreaat.
